&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Skeletons, lasers, tattoo buses — the Torq brand grabs attention like nothing else in cybersecurity. And we&#39;re growing like crazy, backed by Series D funding, 200% employee growth, and 300% revenue growth. Fueling Torq&#39;s momentum is our game-changing AI SOC platform, backed by a team and culture that makes Torq one of Forbes&#39; Best Startup Employers in America, and a Business Insider &#39;startup to bet your career on&#39;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Life at Torq is all gas, no brakes. We&#39;re a team of relentless, collaborative go-getters pushing the boundaries of what&#39;s possible for security automation. Every role is an essential driver of Torq&#39;s success as the AI-native autonomous SecOps platform of choice for security teams across the Fortune 500.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Business Development Representative (BDR) to play a critical role in our sales organization, generate new business opportunities, and qualify leads for the sales team. As a key contributor to our growing organization, you&#39;ll have the unique opportunity to help build and shape our sales processes, strategies, and tactics from the ground up. &lt;strong&gt;This is a remote position based in Dallas metro.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What you will do:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate leads and build relationships by nurturing prospects and finding new potential sales outlets; cold calls, LinkedIn and email outreach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain a pipeline of potential customers and opportunities that ensure lead quality and quantity while qualifying and prioritizing inbound leads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct research on target accounts and industries to better understand their cybersecurity challenges and needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the sales team to develop and execute account-based sales strategies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Occasional attendance to industry &amp;amp; networking events in assigned region.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use CRM software tools to track leads, opportunities, and activities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage time effectively, meet personal goals, and work effectively with members of the assigned territory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What you should bring to the table:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preferably 1+ years of experience as an SDR/BDR, in a growth stage startup or a cyber security company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative problem-solving approach and strong interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of consistent success, leadership, and ability to take ownership of responsibilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to self-motivate, prioritize and manage unstructured time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with CRM software (preferably Salesforce) and sales automation tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team player mentality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an equal opportunity employer, we are committed to a team defined and empowered by diversity. We consider qualified applicants without regard to race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status or disability status.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-Remote&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;We build AI for a living,&amp;nbsp; and we encourage candidates to use it to prep, research, and sharpen their best work. But we&#39;re hiring humans, not chatbots. We want the real you.&amp;nbsp; Use AI to tighten your resume, prep for interviews, research Torq, and outline ideas for written responses. Show up as yourself for live interviews, final assessments (the voice, logic, and reasoning need to be yours), and anywhere we&#39;re evaluating how you think — not how you prompt.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Skeletons, lasers, tattoo buses — the Torq brand grabs attention like nothing else in cybersecurity. And we&#39;re growing like crazy, backed by Series D funding, 200% employee growth, and 300% revenue growth. Fueling Torq&#39;s momentum is our game-changing AI SOC platform, backed by a team and culture that makes Torq one of Forbes&#39; Best Startup Employers in America, and a Business Insider &#39;startup to bet your career on&#39;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Life at Torq is all gas, no brakes. We&#39;re a team of relentless, collaborative go-getters pushing the boundaries of what&#39;s possible for security automation. Every role is an essential driver of Torq&#39;s success as the AI-native autonomous SecOps platform of choice for security teams across the Fortune 500.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Intelligence Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Remote/USA&lt;br&gt;Department: Product Marketing&lt;br&gt;Manager: Sr Director, Product Marketing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The AI SOC market is moving fast and the competition is watching us just as closely as we’re watching them. As Torq’s Competitive Intelligence Manager, you are the eyes and ears of the organization, transforming a multitude of market signals into the strategic advantage that keeps our GTM one step ahead. You will own competitive intelligence, ensuring that it accurately reflects AI SOC competitors’ capabilities and anticipates movements so that our Sales, Product, and Leadership teams are never caught off guard&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage Competitive Intelligence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather competitive intelligence from all available sources, including analyst reports, news wires, competitor communications, customer reviews, partner conversations, field intelligence, and AI-assisted tools (e.g., Crayon, Klue).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain battlecards for Tier 1, 2, and 3 competitors in the AI SOC market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anticipate competitor movement, especially for Tier 1, and proactively brief stakeholders and leadership as we continuously pressure-test and sharpen our own strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct deep-dive SWOT analyses and build structured frameworks that map competitor features, pricing models, and opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enable Global Sales&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously update competitive battlecards, including crisp “What to Say” guidance, so that sales have the right words for every competitive scenario, from first call to final selection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate latest findings to global sales and sales engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anticipate and proactively answer questions that sellers face in competitive evaluations, and be the SME who can jump on a live deal call at a moment’s notice to tilt the balance in Torq’s favor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize structured win/loss interviews with buyers and partner with sales leadership in field debrief sessions, to deliver key insights to Product Marketing for messaging refinement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prove Cross-Functional Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Synthesize key competitive intelligence findings into coherent presentations to leadership across Marketing, Sales, Customer Success, and Product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product Management to translate competitive gaps and whitespace opportunities into informed roadmap decisions that ensure the Torq AI SOC Platform evolves faster than the competition can follow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track competitive win rate

