&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build trusted relationships with enterprise CISOs, CIOs, Boards, and security executives across North America.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with account teams on strategic enterprise opportunities and key customer engagements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise customers on security operations modernization, AI-driven security workflows, threat response, and operational resilience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent customer perspectives internally to influence product strategy and go-to-market priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Revenue &amp;amp; Go-To-Market Partnership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a strategic advisor to the CRO and sales leadership team on enterprise market trends and competitive positioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support complex sales cycles through executive briefings, workshops, architecture discussions, and strategic advisory sessions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help develop differentiated messaging for Fortune 500 and large enterprise accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with marketing on thought leadership campaigns, webinars, analyst engagements, and industry events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Industry Leadership &amp;amp; Evangelism&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a visible external voice for Torq at conferences, executive roundtables, podcasts, and customer events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Publish and present perspectives on SecOps automation, AI in cybersecurity, SOC transformation, and operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships with analysts, strategic partners, and cybersecurity communities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
