&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an AI-savvy Product Manager to join Torq as we continue expanding and exploring the hottest intersection in the security market: agentic AI and SecOps. The ideal candidate will have both experience in at least one SOC-adjacent domain (threat intelligence, SecOps, hunting, incident response…) and strong understanding of agentic AI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll own parts of Torq’s agentic platform: where agents are managed, how they interact with users, and how they can help SOCs to reduce system-critical metrics and overall threat exposure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead critical parts of Torq’s agentic platform to help drive forward adoption and innovation across the full lifecycle - from UX to prompt engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become an expert in Torq’s AI SOC offering and in Torq’s Platform as a whole&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the customer’s voice inside Torq to ensure we’re staying on the critical path&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Torq’s top-notch engineering teams to deliver product capabilities and stay on top of state-of-the-art AI trends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze product data - from classic product analytics to AI evaluations of usage patterns - to proactively bubble up user needs or issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ideal Candidate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has 3-5 years of product management experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possesses a strong understanding of agentic / LLM products - from UX to the technical LLM engineering stack&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spent at least 2 years working in the cybersecurity market, ideally in a SOC-adjacent space (SecOps, incident response, threat intelligence, threat hunting)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensively worked with automation products and APIs - can look under the hood and understand systems and architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data-driven, with the ability to ask the right questions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Superb English speaking and writing skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an equal-opportunity employer, we are committed to a team defined and empowered by diversity. We consider qualified applicants without regard to race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are waiting for you!&lt;/p&gt;
